snippet: The technical errors that had bedeviled visitors to the site for weeks seemed to have been tamed, and applicants were finally selecting health care plans under the Affordable Care Act.
abstract: Interviews reveal vast improvements to federal healthcare Web site, with users reporting far fewer errors a week after deadline set by Pres Obama for fixing the system.

byline.original: By LIZETTE ALVAREZ and JENNIFER PRESTON
byline.contributor: Lizette Alvarez reported from Miami, and Jennifer Preston from New York. Robert Pear and Sharon LaFraniere contributed reporting from Washington, and Dan Frosch from Denver.

lead_paragraph: The technical errors that had bedeviled visitors to the site for weeks seemed to have been tamed, and applicants were finally selecting health care plans under the Affordable Care Act.

headline.main: Health Care Exchange Is Vastly Improved, Users Say
